 :tx/rationale "DESIGN DECISION: For dead-wiring prevention, the structural test (INV-REFLEXIVE-004) is the correct integration point, not automod or a new braid command. Reasoning: (1) The test runs in the existing cargo test pipeline which is already a mandatory quality gate. (2) Zero new dependencies — braid-kernel has no proc-macro deps and shouldn't add one for this. (3) Self-documenting — failure message explains the fix. (4) The test IS a projection — it derives the expected module list from the filesystem and compares to mod.rs, which is the correct DDIS pattern (projection over independent maintenance). (5) Compile-time prevention via automod would save ~0 seconds in practice (cargo test runs on every change). The three-layer guard is: Prevention = the test itself (catches at next cargo test, <1 min latency). Detection = clippy unreachable_pub (partial coverage). Correction = harvest methodology gap counter for unreachable tested functions."
